reviews.review_text: killer show This is my favorite version of the auds here. The energy level of the band for this show was crazy. Listen to the Jack Straw Bertha to hear it. The whole first set was awesome but the real fireworks come later. After a good pre-drums the band settles into a fiery Watchtower after Space and it's easily my favorite. Jerry shreds and the whole band ignites, burns brightly, and then fades into ash. And from the ashes rises the great Morning Dew. It peaks, it ebbs, it flows, its everything you could want from a Dew, and more. By the time they rock into Saturday Night we were giddy, dancing and singing in the aisles of the former Knickerbocker Arena. The Knockin' brought us back to earth and sent us out in high anticipation for the next two nights.
